### Root Causes

**Infinite Loop Pattern:**
```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Creates new object every render
const data = useWidgetStore((state) => state.settings[id]?.data || []);

// ✅ CORRECT - Stable selector, fallback outside
const data = useWidgetStore((state) => state.settings[id]?.data) || [];
```

**Why it crashes:**
1. Zustand selector returns NEW `[]` if undefined
2. React detects new reference
3. Component re-renders
4. New `[]` returned AGAIN
5. Infinite loop → "Maximum update depth exceeded" → crash

**Systemic Issue:**
- Same pattern copy-pasted across 6 widgets
- Should have searched entire codebase after first fix
- Found with grep: `useWidgetStore.*\|\|.*[\[\{]`

